WEBVTT

00:06.429 --> 00:08.052
Are you crying?

00:08.570 --> 00:10.381
What, I'm not allowed
to get a little emotional

00:10.405 --> 00:12.156
at a superhero movie?

00:12.181 --> 00:14.952
Lives were lost, Zoey.
Ethical questions were raised.

00:14.977 --> 00:17.188
And yet, not a single character

00:17.212 --> 00:19.284
flapped their arms when they flew.

00:22.029 --> 00:24.178
Oh, good, Max, you're here, too. Scooch.

00:24.203 --> 00:26.297
And we're gonna turn this off.

00:26.321 --> 00:27.832
No, no, no! There's an
amazing scene after the credits.

00:27.856 --> 00:29.321
- We're gonna miss it now.
- If you want to see

00:29.345 --> 00:31.802
grown-ass men run around in unitards,
go to the Castro.

00:32.046 --> 00:34.256
Anyways, I need your help with Eddie.

00:34.281 --> 00:37.209
I slid into his DMs.
That boy is so cryptic.

00:37.234 --> 00:39.076
I asked him if he
wanted to go get drinks,

00:39.101 --> 00:40.244
and he wrote back "K."

00:40.268 --> 00:43.147
He only responds in one letter. "K"?

00:43.171 --> 00:45.913
- Who does that?
- Oh, my God.

00:45.938 --> 00:48.652
- Are you dating Hercules?
- I introduced them.

00:48.677 --> 00:50.254
I'm actually a pretty
exceptional wingman.

00:50.278 --> 00:52.056
Boy, you made one introduction.

00:52.080 --> 00:53.491
You did not officiate the wedding.

00:53.515 --> 00:55.093
Well, I'd be exceptional at that, too,

00:55.117 --> 00:57.261
and it would be my greatest honor.

00:57.285 --> 01:00.164
Zoey, thank you for
reinstating Movie Night.

01:00.188 --> 01:01.906
I really miss getting our hang time in.

01:01.931 --> 01:03.531
Me, too.

01:06.569 --> 01:08.672
You were so helpful with
my dad the other night.

01:08.697 --> 01:12.109
It made me realize that
I need more Max in my life.

01:12.384 --> 01:15.179
And it reminded me that
you need better popcorn,

01:15.203 --> 01:18.038
because that skinny stuff
tastes like buttered sadness.

01:18.917 --> 01:20.917
- Night.
- Night.

01:23.704 --> 01:24.991
What is that look?

01:25.016 --> 01:26.789
You know damn well what this look is.

01:26.814 --> 01:28.125
Reinstating Movie Night,

01:28.150 --> 01:29.806
touching that boy on the shoulder.

01:29.831 --> 01:31.010
You gonna give him the wrong impression,

01:31.034 --> 01:32.912
and we both know Max burns

01:32.937 --> 01:35.548
white hot white boy love for you.

01:36.660 --> 01:40.259
I thought about that,
and then I realized

01:40.284 --> 01:43.400
things only got weird when
I heard him sing to me.

01:43.425 --> 01:45.541
So, if I never got this power,

01:45.566 --> 01:47.915
I'd still be having Movie
Night every week with Max.

01:47.940 --> 01:50.105
Just because that's what's
going on in his head

01:50.130 --> 01:51.507
doesn't mean he's gonna act on it.

01:51.532 --> 01:53.584
Just, let's talk about you, okay?

01:53.608 --> 01:54.974
Hmm.

01:56.445 --> 01:58.556
You just responded "K" back to him?

01:58.580 --> 01:59.860
Hell, yeah.

01:59.885 --> 02:01.328
You wanna play games, Eddie?

02:01.353 --> 02:03.157
Let's play games.

02:05.680 --> 02:08.181
Okay. All right.

02:08.205 --> 02:09.783
- You got it?
- Yeah.

02:09.809 --> 02:11.620
Okay.

02:11.645 --> 02:14.345
Hold on a sec. I wanna
make sure he has extra support.

02:14.370 --> 02:16.835
Oh, so like, the opposite of
what you did for me and Emily.

02:16.860 --> 02:19.117
Maybe if you would've told
Emily how you were feeling,

02:19.142 --> 02:21.312
about the baby coming,
instead of acting like a baby,

02:21.336 --> 02:23.081
she wouldn't have asked for
my opinion in the first place.

02:23.105 --> 02:25.415
The opinion I told you
very clearly not to give?

02:25.440 --> 02:26.648
- That opinion?
- Um...

02:26.673 --> 02:29.306
Could I speak to you both privately?

02:32.709 --> 02:33.977
What is it? I gotta get to work.

02:34.001 --> 02:36.056
And I gotta get to any
room that he's not in.

02:39.743 --> 02:44.009
♪ A little less conversation,
a little more action, please ♪

02:44.034 --> 02:48.415
♪ All this aggravation
ain't satisfactioning me ♪

02:48.440 --> 02:50.874
♪ A little more bite
and a little less bark ♪

02:50.899 --> 02:53.044
♪ A little less fight
and a little more spark ♪

02:53.068 --> 02:57.180
♪ Close your mouth and open up
your heart and baby satisfy me ♪

02:57.205 --> 02:59.717
♪ Satisfy me, baby ♪

02:59.741 --> 03:02.386
♪ Come on, come on, come on, come on ♪

03:02.410 --> 03:04.622
♪ Come on, come on, come on, come on ♪

03:04.646 --> 03:07.147
♪ Come on, come on, come on, come on ♪

03:08.405 --> 03:11.251
♪ Hey, a little more bite
and a little less bark ♪

03:11.276 --> 03:13.387
♪ A little less fight
and a little more spark ♪

03:13.412 --> 03:17.092
♪ Close your mouth and open up
your heart and baby satisfy me ♪

03:17.117 --> 03:19.484
♪ Satisfy me ♪

03:23.098 --> 03:25.143
Um, Mom?

03:25.167 --> 03:26.811
Can we help you with something?

03:26.835 --> 03:29.226
As a matter of fact, you can.

03:29.251 --> 03:30.970
I need you to get over

03:30.995 --> 03:33.000
this childish thing
that you're both doing

03:33.025 --> 03:35.134
and stop fighting in
front of your father.

03:35.159 --> 03:36.970
I mean, things are hard enough already,

03:36.995 --> 03:39.874
especially now that I have decided

03:39.899 --> 03:42.000
to hire a full-time caregiver.

03:42.025 --> 03:44.929
And I know that's the right
and logical medical decision

03:44.953 --> 03:47.498
but it's just... hard to accept

03:47.522 --> 03:49.923
that I can't do this all
on my own anymore.

03:49.948 --> 03:53.681
Mom, please do not feel guilty.

03:53.898 --> 03:55.876
He can't walk anymore.

03:55.901 --> 03:57.907
- Yeah, and you can't carry him.
- I know.

03:57.932 --> 04:00.400
I'm still wrapping my
head around all of it.

04:00.425 --> 04:02.403
Don't worry. We will
find the best caregiver

04:02.428 --> 04:04.239
in the whole city and I'll help you.

04:04.264 --> 04:06.212
That would be great. I've already set up

04:06.237 --> 04:07.751
some interviews for this afternoon,

04:07.776 --> 04:09.120
so you can join me.

04:09.144 --> 04:11.040
- Okay.
- Okay.

04:11.065 --> 04:13.220
What am I gonna do about the two of you?

04:15.559 --> 04:16.695
I'll try to let it go.

04:16.720 --> 04:19.942
I mean, I guess you did
kinda help me and Emily

04:19.968 --> 04:22.912
talk about some things
and work through them.

04:22.937 --> 04:24.754
I'm sorry, I can't quite hear you.

04:24.779 --> 04:29.239
Are you saying that I
actually helped you?

04:29.264 --> 04:31.684
I'm saying that we
share the same mother,

04:31.709 --> 04:33.578
and I like to see her happy.

04:33.602 --> 04:35.568
I like it when you're happy, too.

04:39.028 --> 04:40.873
- Morning.
- Morning.

04:41.324 --> 04:42.575
We still on for lunch?

04:42.600 --> 04:44.055
Yeah, but let's try
something different today.

04:44.079 --> 04:45.178
How about a food court?

04:45.203 --> 04:46.657
I didn't peg you for a food court guy.

04:46.681 --> 04:48.648
Yeah, well, I love me some options.

04:59.724 --> 05:01.811
Dude, killer party.

05:01.836 --> 05:04.074
And that massive charcuterie board?

05:04.099 --> 05:06.399
- Pretty epic.
- Thanks.

05:06.995 --> 05:08.795
How about that smoked gouda?

05:09.393 --> 05:10.526
Hmm.

05:11.706 --> 05:14.518
How about those smoked roses?

05:20.748 --> 05:22.467
Zoey, you got a minute?

05:25.506 --> 05:27.576
I'm sorry about the roses comment.

05:27.601 --> 05:31.825
And the actual roses.
Both things, really.

05:31.849 --> 05:33.327
I was thinking about
texting you this weekend,

05:33.351 --> 05:35.372
and then I realized
that's kind of what got us

05:35.397 --> 05:36.807
into this mess in the first place.

05:36.831 --> 05:37.987
Well, however it started,

05:38.012 --> 05:39.443
I realized that I have
been leaning on you

05:39.467 --> 05:41.045
way too much about my dad stuff,

05:41.069 --> 05:42.363
which is why I think

05:42.388 --> 05:44.182
we just gotta go back
to being co-workers.

05:44.207 --> 05:46.988
Think it'll help keep things
aboveboard and professional.

05:47.276 --> 05:49.080
I totally agree.

05:49.105 --> 05:50.233
- All right.
- We are gonna be

05:50.257 --> 05:52.457
ultra-professional from now on.

05:54.355 --> 05:56.652
And with that, I bid you good day.

06:00.981 --> 06:02.519
I never look at her in the eyes, anyway,

06:02.543 --> 06:04.402
but I feel like I should maybe today.

06:04.702 --> 06:05.702
I'm gonna try it.

06:05.727 --> 06:07.058
What's the crisis? Did I cause it?

06:07.082 --> 06:08.372
This is literally gonna blow your mind,

06:08.396 --> 06:10.341
but Joan and Charlie
are getting a divorce.

06:10.365 --> 06:12.910
It's all over the tech news.
Can you believe it?

06:13.519 --> 06:16.313
Apparently you can and
perhaps already knew?

06:17.030 --> 06:19.291
I think I'm gonna be
sick. Joan and Charlie

06:19.316 --> 06:21.332
were the closest thing we
have to American royalty.

06:21.357 --> 06:23.277
I was this close to getting
commemorative plates.

06:23.302 --> 06:24.989
What do you guys think
she did to drive him away?

06:25.013 --> 06:27.269
Did you ever think that
maybe it was Charlie's fault?

06:27.294 --> 06:28.806
Charlie's only fault was
making a video game

06:28.830 --> 06:30.327
I sat and played for so many hours

06:30.352 --> 06:31.908
I had to get my baby toe amputated.

06:31.933 --> 06:34.165
- You did?
- Two-thirds.

06:34.189 --> 06:37.268
Hi. Everyone having a fun gossip sesh

06:37.292 --> 06:39.270
about the boss's marriage? I want in.

06:39.294 --> 06:40.838
Guys, don't fall for it. She's the boss.

06:40.862 --> 06:43.774
Relax, I know the news
of my divorce broke today

06:43.798 --> 06:46.844
because I had my publicist
plant it along with

06:46.868 --> 06:49.413
a photo of me in hot riding pants

06:49.437 --> 06:52.316
and Charlie in Tevas at a Phish concert.

06:52.341 --> 06:54.129
So Leif and I have come up with

06:54.154 --> 06:57.316
a fantastic idea that's gonna
blow your minds. Let's go.

06:58.019 --> 07:00.223
You may recall Simon's engagement party,

07:00.248 --> 07:02.526
where Zoey tried to burn the place down.

07:02.550 --> 07:04.261
Well, while that was going on,

07:04.285 --> 07:07.604
Leif and I came up with an idea

07:07.629 --> 07:10.244
that we think is going to
be pretty revolutionary.

07:10.269 --> 07:12.393
It's called The Chirp.

07:12.418 --> 07:14.426
- The Chirp!
- Don't do that.

07:14.451 --> 07:17.574
So, The Chirp is a Bluetooth
earpiece with a high-res camera.

07:17.599 --> 07:20.878
It uses AI and facial
recognition technology

07:20.902 --> 07:23.893
to gather information on
everything the user sees.

07:23.918 --> 07:26.083
It'll search public and
personal databases,

07:26.107 --> 07:28.433
filter the results,
and then chirp in your ear

07:28.458 --> 07:30.553
the exact thing you need
to know in real time.

07:30.578 --> 07:33.902
No more forgetting the name of
your coworker's forgettable husband.

07:33.927 --> 07:36.019
Or wondering what brand of kale chips

07:36.044 --> 07:37.288
the man next to you is eating

07:37.313 --> 07:39.079
when you're both out
birdwatching together.

07:39.921 --> 07:42.261
'Kay. We'll work on the examples.

07:42.286 --> 07:44.917
That sounds great.

07:45.198 --> 07:47.298
How would you like the
team to take it from here?

07:47.323 --> 07:50.107
Well, I think Leif and I are
just fine on our own for now,

07:50.131 --> 07:52.472
but we'll let you know
what we need in the future

07:52.497 --> 07:55.343
and until then,
stop gawking and start coding.

07:55.624 --> 07:57.113
Get to work.

07:57.464 --> 07:58.681
Um, Joan?

07:58.706 --> 08:01.318
Could I, um,
just talk to you for a second?

08:01.342 --> 08:03.120
Um, I wanted to talk about The Chirp.

08:03.144 --> 08:06.424
- Ah.
- Since I am technically

08:06.448 --> 08:11.607
Leif's... supervisor,
you don't want me to...

08:11.632 --> 08:13.597
No, just sit tight.

08:13.621 --> 08:15.166
We're working so closely on it,

08:15.190 --> 08:17.133
I think we're just gonna cook
it a little while longer.

08:17.157 --> 08:18.882
We'll let you know if
we need you, thanks.

08:21.865 --> 08:23.273
Okay.

08:23.298 --> 08:25.543
Leif. Bro?

08:25.567 --> 08:28.265
I am so proud of you right now.

08:28.290 --> 08:30.310
But... why didn't you tell me?

08:30.335 --> 08:32.419
Sorry, it was all on
a need-to-know basis.

08:32.443 --> 08:34.618
The time I got to second
base with my third cousin

08:34.642 --> 08:36.607
was a need-to-know basis,
but I told you about it.

08:36.633 --> 08:38.562
I've just been really busy
with The Chirp, okay?

08:39.082 --> 08:40.423
But hey, I'll make it up to you

08:40.448 --> 08:42.126
when we celebrate
the Spell-iversary, right?

08:42.150 --> 08:43.429
Now we're talking.

08:43.453 --> 08:46.830
Everybody, as you all know,
Spell-iversary is...

08:46.855 --> 08:48.732
The day you both celebrate winning

08:48.756 --> 08:51.402
the National Spelling Bee at age 11.

08:51.426 --> 08:53.304
Yeah, you only
tell us about it every year.

08:53.329 --> 08:55.585
Well, excuse us, you ischiocerite.

08:55.610 --> 08:57.421
- Ishy-occshu-what?
- Sorry.

08:57.446 --> 08:58.975
You need a country of origin, bro?

08:59.000 --> 09:00.644
Or you want me to use it in a sentence?

09:00.668 --> 09:01.979
Hey, Leif, I bet these troglodytes

09:02.003 --> 09:04.358
wouldn't make it past round
three, am I right?

09:07.830 --> 09:11.030
Hey, uh, what's a good
word for "hung out to dry"?

09:12.483 --> 09:14.398
"Repudiated."

09:14.681 --> 09:17.646
- Leif looked so smug today.
- Yeah.

09:17.671 --> 09:19.240
With his evil little grin

09:19.265 --> 09:21.710
and his well-tailored pants.
He's clearly doing all of this

09:21.735 --> 09:22.761
to get back at me for the peer reviews

09:22.785 --> 09:24.483
and I wasn't even the
one who dinged him.

09:25.327 --> 09:27.202
Max, are you okay?

09:27.227 --> 09:30.607
You look... pale... er than usual.

09:30.632 --> 09:32.858
No, I'm fine. I'm actually...

09:32.883 --> 09:35.280
I'm actually really, uh, happy.

09:35.305 --> 09:36.937
You don't look happy.

09:36.962 --> 09:38.615
You look ill.

09:38.640 --> 09:40.999
Everything's okay, it's just...

09:41.823 --> 09:45.889
♪ Everything means nothing
if I can't have you ♪

09:45.914 --> 09:50.127
♪ I can't write one song
that's not about you ♪

09:50.151 --> 09:54.098
♪ Can't drink without
thinking about you ♪

09:54.122 --> 09:57.468
♪ Is it too late to tell you that ♪

09:57.492 --> 10:00.655
♪ Everything means nothing
if I can't have you? ♪

10:00.680 --> 10:03.248
Oh, no, I did give you
the wrong impression.

10:03.273 --> 10:06.937
♪ Oh, I'm good at keeping my distance ♪

10:06.962 --> 10:10.813
♪ I know that you're the
feeling I'm missing ♪

10:10.838 --> 10:14.785
♪ You know that I hate to admit it ♪

10:14.809 --> 10:18.122
♪ But everything means
nothing if I can't have you ♪

10:18.146 --> 10:19.187
Wow, this is a big number.

10:19.212 --> 10:21.178
You must really be feeling this one.

10:21.817 --> 10:27.063
♪ Oo-oo, I can't write one
song that's not about you ♪

10:27.088 --> 10:30.901
♪ Can't drink without
thinking about you ♪

10:30.925 --> 10:33.971
♪ Is it too late to tell you that... ♪

10:33.995 --> 10:35.124
We were having such a nice time.

10:35.148 --> 10:37.405
Why'd you have to go and sing to me?

10:37.873 --> 10:39.796
You said you wanted
more Max in your life.

10:39.821 --> 10:42.490
- Well, I want that too!
- ♪... not about you ♪

10:42.515 --> 10:45.249
♪ Can't drink without
thinking about... ♪

10:45.274 --> 10:47.084
Wait, you can actually hear me?

10:47.108 --> 10:49.786
- ♪ Is it too late to tell you that ♪
- What does that mean?

10:49.811 --> 10:53.741
♪ Everything means nothing
if I can't have you ♪

10:59.387 --> 11:01.904
- Oh, my God, this is actual life.
- I know, right?

11:01.929 --> 11:03.801
And we only had like three rehearsals.

11:03.825 --> 11:05.603
There's this whole
online flash mob service.

11:05.627 --> 11:07.960
- This isn't even a real baby.
- It's not.

11:07.985 --> 11:09.913
I have fliers if you want.

11:10.671 --> 11:13.943
This is unexpected, and amazing,

11:13.968 --> 11:17.381
but, um, I'm very confused
and I have to go.

11:17.405 --> 11:18.771
I'm sorry.

11:19.679 --> 11:22.460
That's not usually a very good sign.

11:22.809 --> 11:26.789
That was some real messed up...

11:27.667 --> 11:30.535
Synced & corrected by QueenMaddie
www.addic7ed.com

11:37.523 --> 11:39.526
You okay? You look shaken.

11:39.566 --> 11:40.824
What?

11:40.849 --> 11:42.938
Oh, yeah, uh...

11:43.541 --> 11:45.346
Today has been... nope.

11:45.371 --> 11:48.387
Nope, nope.
We are "keeping it professional."

11:48.702 --> 11:50.510
This is not business-related.

11:50.535 --> 11:52.979
Yes, right. My bad.

11:53.004 --> 11:54.160
Carry on.

11:54.481 --> 11:55.902
Thanks.

11:58.244 --> 12:00.082
Ooh. Zoey?

12:02.691 --> 12:05.019
I know that you're upset
about not being included

12:05.044 --> 12:07.596
in The Chirp so far, but you will be.

12:07.621 --> 12:08.854
It's just a matter of time.

12:08.879 --> 12:11.174
That's great. I'm great. It's all great.

12:11.199 --> 12:13.801
I am also great. I mean, I will be.

12:13.826 --> 12:16.354
Now that the news of the
divorce is made public,

12:16.379 --> 12:19.142
I really need to pump the brakes
on some of the bad behavior...

12:19.580 --> 12:20.963
Excessive drinking,

12:20.988 --> 12:24.465
buying a ranch in Montana
to go with my riding pants.

12:25.065 --> 12:26.276
Oops.

12:26.301 --> 12:30.846
But I feel great and I'm
gonna be totally fine.

12:30.871 --> 12:32.688
- Really?
- Mm-hmm!

12:33.301 --> 12:34.824
Well...

12:34.848 --> 12:37.323
- onwards and upwards, then.
- Right?

12:37.348 --> 12:40.018
Who knows? Maybe I'll even try
getting out there, you know.

12:40.043 --> 12:43.471
Charlie and I only had
sex 3 1/2 times last year.

12:43.496 --> 12:44.893
How pathetic is that?

12:44.918 --> 12:47.957
I'm sorry, I'm stuck on the... half.

12:47.982 --> 12:50.561
When Richard Branson calls
"Time for dinner,"

12:50.586 --> 12:52.144
and you're staying
at his private island,

12:52.168 --> 12:54.496
you stop what you're doing
and you go to dinner.

12:55.078 --> 12:57.680
Ooh, Richard Branson.
Wonder if he's single.

12:58.016 --> 12:59.180
Can you Google that for me?

12:59.205 --> 13:00.946
- Of course.
- Thank you.

13:01.602 --> 13:06.014
These are the best candidates
that can start work immediately.

13:06.039 --> 13:08.858
All we need to find is someone competent

13:08.882 --> 13:12.608
and responsible and trustworthy

13:12.633 --> 13:14.897
and experienced.

13:14.921 --> 13:17.370
So basically we're looking
for an angel sent from heaven.

13:17.641 --> 13:20.706
- Yeah.
- Yeah. Okay. Yeah. Sure.

13:20.731 --> 13:24.112
What would you say is your
approach to in-home caregiving?

13:24.137 --> 13:27.432
Well, I provide a whole-body approach.

13:27.457 --> 13:29.101
To caregiving?

13:29.667 --> 13:31.486
Oh, yeah.

13:32.954 --> 13:35.933
Sorry, it's hard to concentrate

13:35.958 --> 13:37.736
with all the dark
energies in this house.

13:37.884 --> 13:39.964
Was someone murdered? Recently?

13:39.989 --> 13:41.572
No, two people.

13:42.159 --> 13:44.009
Sisters.

13:44.034 --> 13:45.565
My approach?

13:45.590 --> 13:46.948
I don't know, that's a thinker.

13:46.973 --> 13:49.901
Ah, I don't know,
I guess I'd say "needs-based."

13:49.926 --> 13:52.198
Like, if he needs to eat, let him eat.

13:52.223 --> 13:54.964
If he needs to sleep, let him sleep.

