Okay, uh, what would
you think about incorporating

13:59.798 --> 14:03.460
some type of exercise
routine into his life?

14:04.942 --> 14:08.382
What is he training for,
the New York marathon?

14:09.742 --> 14:11.156
I hate to break it to you, pal.

14:11.181 --> 14:12.710
I think you're gonna lose.

14:12.735 --> 14:15.734
What you should be
doing is online poker.

14:15.759 --> 14:18.343
It's all about sitting
at a table for hours.

14:18.368 --> 14:19.719
Guy with nowhere to go?

14:19.743 --> 14:21.039
He could make a killing.

14:24.403 --> 14:26.351
I see you're a registered nurse?

14:26.376 --> 14:28.164
Yes, for 29 years.

14:28.531 --> 14:31.749
That's amazing. So, um...

14:31.774 --> 14:34.812
How are you gonna celebrate
your 30th anniversary?

14:34.837 --> 14:36.615
Extending someone's life.

14:37.220 --> 14:38.398
How festive.

14:38.423 --> 14:39.765
I've worked with several patients

14:39.790 --> 14:41.960
with degenerative diseases.

14:41.985 --> 14:44.304
It's all about providing
proper nutrition

14:44.329 --> 14:46.984
and instituting a physiotherapy routine

14:47.009 --> 14:48.420
to avoid muscle atrophy.

14:48.445 --> 14:49.758
My goal is to keep your loved one

14:49.782 --> 14:52.398
as healthy as I can
for as long as I can.

14:56.065 --> 14:58.532
So Nancy, when can you start?

15:04.818 --> 15:06.281
- Hi.
- Hi.

15:06.306 --> 15:07.951
Are you seriously hiding from me?

15:07.976 --> 15:09.687
No. I work in here all the time.

15:09.712 --> 15:11.712
Jamming on code, listening to tunes.

15:14.410 --> 15:17.195
This is a podcast on
the Golden State Killer.

15:17.220 --> 15:20.789
I listen to true crime
to calm myself. Uh...

15:21.195 --> 15:24.054
I'm sorry I just ran away.

15:24.079 --> 15:26.046
That was an amazing gesture.

15:26.071 --> 15:28.578
So amazing that it instantly
repelled you from me?

15:28.603 --> 15:31.482
'Cause I really did put
myself out there, Zo,

15:31.507 --> 15:33.070
and I'd appreciate it if you could do

15:33.095 --> 15:35.171
or say something in return.

15:35.196 --> 15:36.203
Look we both know

15:36.228 --> 15:37.874
I am not good with
feelings and emotions,

15:37.899 --> 15:39.804
and this is just a lot
for me to handle right...

15:39.829 --> 15:41.204
Okay, well,
you can't just leave me hanging.

15:41.228 --> 15:43.507
I really don't get you lately.

15:43.532 --> 15:46.144
I mean, you've been acting
weird for months now.

15:46.169 --> 15:48.546
One minute you're here,
the next minute you drift off

15:48.571 --> 15:51.445
into this... this Zoeyland,
and I just can't figure out

15:51.470 --> 15:53.110
what the hell's going
on in your head anymore.

15:53.134 --> 15:55.546
- Is this all 'cause of your dad?
- No.

15:55.571 --> 15:57.243
- It's not just my dad.
- Okay, then what is it?

15:57.267 --> 15:59.329
- Just tell me. I can handle it.
- It's not that I don't want

15:59.353 --> 16:00.430
to have that conversation.

16:00.455 --> 16:03.281
It's that I can't, really.

16:03.306 --> 16:06.018
Zoey, I just told you I loved you.

16:06.591 --> 16:08.682
I literally just sang my heart
out in front of a mall...

16:08.706 --> 16:10.512
I have a superpower! Okay?

16:12.114 --> 16:13.114
Okay, forget it.

16:13.139 --> 16:14.726
You know, you could have just
told me you weren't interested.

16:14.750 --> 16:16.428
- That probably would've hurt...
- I'm serious.

16:16.452 --> 16:18.380
I hear people's inner thoughts.

16:18.405 --> 16:21.130
They sing them to me, constantly.

16:21.155 --> 16:23.341
That's why I'm off in Zoeyland.

16:23.366 --> 16:25.216
I'm not who you think I am.

16:25.241 --> 16:27.286
I am a mutant.

16:27.311 --> 16:29.481
I am the X-Men

16:29.506 --> 16:31.911
meets "The Voice."

16:32.754 --> 16:34.687
Now do you understand?

16:35.398 --> 16:37.301
I'm sorry, what?!

16:40.349 --> 16:42.011
Okay, let me get this straight.

16:42.036 --> 16:43.781
I do this whole big flash mob

16:43.805 --> 16:45.316
where I confess how I really feel to you

16:45.340 --> 16:47.184
and you respond with
stories of earthquakes,

16:47.208 --> 16:48.552
magical x-ray machines,

16:48.576 --> 16:50.387
and endless musical
numbers in your head?

16:50.411 --> 16:52.456
Yes, it was actually
a magic MRI machine.

16:52.480 --> 16:54.131
Somehow that doesn't
make me feel any better.

16:54.155 --> 16:56.378
- Imagine how I feel.
- Should I imagine it?

16:56.403 --> 16:59.098
- Or should I just belt it out?
- This isn't a joke.

16:59.123 --> 17:02.704
You have no idea how this
has taken over my life.

17:02.729 --> 17:05.762
If this is really happening, then
what am I singing right now? Huh?

17:06.550 --> 17:07.741
You're not singing anything.

17:07.766 --> 17:09.800
What about Sam, what's he singing?

17:11.111 --> 17:12.755
